# Build-time secret for baking your REAL GitHub contribution calendar + yearly
# total into the recent-activity section (scripts/build-github-activity.mjs).
#
# Use a READ-ONLY token: a fine-grained PAT (no extra scopes needed for public
# contributions) or a classic PAT with `read:user`. It is used only at build
# time and is never shipped to the browser — only the resulting public numbers
# are baked into the static output.
#
# For production, set the same variable in the Vercel project's Environment
# Variables. Locally, copy this file to `.env` (which is git-ignored) or run:
#   GH_CONTRIB_TOKEN=xxxx npm run build:site
#
# Without it, the panel honestly shows just your public repo count (no grid).
GH_CONTRIB_TOKEN=
